span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ <span class=\"fn\">p</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">P</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Eval/Defs.html#Polynomial.map\">Polynomial.map</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Quotient/Defs.html#Ideal.Quotient.mk\">Quotient.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#Ideal.comap\">comap</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial.C\">Polynomial.C</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span>)</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">p</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This technical lemma asserts the existence of a polynomial `p` in an ideal `P ⊂ R[x]`\nthat is non-zero in the quotient `R / (P ∩ R) [x]`.  The assumptions are equivalent to\n`P ≠ 0` and `P ∩ R = (0)`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/GoingUp.html#Ideal.exists_nonzero_mem_of_ne_bot","kind":"theorem","line":101,"name":"Ideal.exists_nonzero_mem_of_ne_bot","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/GoingUp.lean#L101-L115"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/GoingUp.html#Ideal.quotient_mk_maps_eq\"><span class=\"name\">Ideal</span>.<span class=\"name\">quotient_mk_maps_eq</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span c