 href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Eval/Defs.html#Polynomial.mapRingHom\">Polynomial.mapRingHom</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Quotient/Defs.html#Ideal.Quotient.mk\">Quotient.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#Ideal.comap\">comap</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial.C\">Polynomial.C</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span>)</span>)</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">P</span>)</span>\n        <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Eval/Defs.html#Polynomial.mapRingHom\">Polynomial.mapRingHom</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Quotient/Defs.html#Ideal.Quotient.mk\">Quotient.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#Ideal.comap\">comap</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial.C\">Polynomial.C</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span>)</span>)</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom.comp\">comp</a></span>\n    <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Quotient/Defs.html#Ideal.Quotient.mk\">Quotient.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom.comp\">comp</a></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial.C\">Polynomial.C</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The identity in this lemma asserts that the \"obvious\" square\n```\n    R    → (R / (P ∩ R))\n    ↓          ↓\nR[x] / P → (R / (P ∩ R))[x] / (P / (P ∩ R))\n```\ncommutes.  It is used, for instance, in the proof of `quotient_mk_comp_C_is_integral_of_jacobson`,\nin the file `Mathlib/RingTheory/Jacobson/Polynomial.lean`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/GoingUp.html#Ideal.quotient_mk_maps_eq","kind":"theorem","line":83,"name":"Ideal.quotient_mk_maps_eq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d0